  "text": "Pre-steady-state cleavage of 5 0 32 P-labeled rCAUAUCGCC substrate was performed as described in 20 mM Tris-HCl containing 0-30 mM MgCl 2 using L-3 ribozyme [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] except that folding and substrate cleavage were done at 37 C (Figure S1B) , and the end of the burst phase (first turnover) was determined to be 20 s ( Figure S1C ). To verify that the RNA was fully equilibrated, another set of assays was done in which the ribozyme was folded 10-15 min at 50 C, then cooled to 37 C for at least 15 min before addition of the substrate oligonucleotide. Folding transitions under these two conditions were identical for all tested samples within experimental uncertainty ( Figure S1E ). Equilibrium Hydroxyl Radical Footprinting Fe(II)-EDTA-dependent hydroxyl radical cleavage reactions were carried out as previously described by [CITATION_4] , except that 5 0 32 P-labeled RNA was folded 30-40 min at 37 C and incubated 5 min on ice, before the addition of Fenton reagents. The intensities of the cleavage products were corrected and quantified as described previously by [CITATION_5] . To ensure that protections indicate the equilibrium population distribution, experiments were repeated with ribozymes folded 20 min in 50 C and cooled down to 37 C for at least 20 min before footprinting. The protection profiles were identical.",
